---
const props = Astro.props;
const { data } = props;

---

<div id="region-details" class="my-8" >
    
    <!-- Accordion Container -->
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-8">
      <!-- The Political Weather -->
      <div class="accordion-item bg-white border border-[#FEE96A]/30 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
        <button class="accordion-trigger w-full px-6 py-4 text-left  bg-[#FEE96A]/10 hover:bg-[#FEE96A]/20 transition-colors flex justify-between items-center">
          <div class="flex items-center space-x-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" x="0px" y="0px" width="64" height="64" viewBox="0 0 64 64" stroke="currentColor" class="w-8 h-8 text-[#064161]">
              <path d="M 29 7 C 25.686 7 23 9.686 23 13 L 15 13 C 11.686 13 9 15.686 9 19 L 9 45 C 9 48.314 11.686 51 15 51 L 49 51 C 52.314 51 55 48.314 55 45 L 55 19 C 55 15.686 52.314 13 49 13 L 41 13 C 41 9.686 38.314 7 35 7 L 29 7 z M 29 11 L 35 11 C 36.104 11 37 11.895 37 13 L 27 13 C 27 11.895 27.896 11 29 11 z M 15 17 L 49 17 C 50.105 17 51 17.895 51 19 L 51 27.328125 C 47.860304 27.865386 40.276945 29 32 29 C 23.725715 29 16.142076 27.866066 13 27.328125 L 13 19 C 13 17.895 13.895 17 15 17 z M 13 31.384766 C 15.851521 31.855688 20.994182 32.574326 27 32.865234 L 27 33 C 27 34.105 27.895 35 29 35 L 34 35 C 35.105 35 36 34.105 36 33 L 36 32.917969 C 42.43805 32.665598 47.988855 31.881828 51 31.384766 L 51 45 C 51 46.105 50.105 47 49 47 L 15 47 C 13.895 47 13 46.105 13 45 L 13 31.384766 z"></path>
              </svg>
            <h4 class="text-xl text-[#064161]">The Political Weather</h4>
          </div>
          <svg class="accordion-icon w-5 h-5 text-[#064161] transform transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
          </svg>
        </button>
        <div class="accordion-content hidden px-6 py-4">
          <div class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-[#064161] space-y-4">
            <p>
              The 1960s in North America and the UK were marked by upheaval: civil rights struggles in the US, the counterculture wave against the Vietnam War, second-wave feminism, anti-nuclear protests, and a whole generation turning their back on traditional values. In the UK, post-war austerity slowly gave way to consumer culture, youth identity, and a growing hunger for something beyond stiff British formality. These weren’t just backdrops — the unrest and liberation were baked into the music itself, fueling a radical break from both classical tradition and commercial pop.            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- What People Were Hearing -->
      <div class="accordion-item bg-white border border-[#FEE96A]/30 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
        <button class="accordion-trigger w-full px-6 py-4 text-left bg-[#FEE96A]/10 hover:bg-[#FEE96A]/20 transition-colors flex justify-between items-center">
          <div class="flex items-center space-x-3">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-[#064161]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 19V6l12-3v13M9 19c0 1.105-1.343 2-3 2s-3-.895-3-2 1.343-2 3-2 3 .895 3 2zm12-3c0 1.105-1.343 2-3 2s-3-.895-3-2 1.343-2 3-2 3 .895 3 2zM9 10l12-3"></path>
            </svg>
            <h4 class="text-xl text-[#064161]">What People Were Hearing</h4>
          </div>
          <svg class="accordion-icon w-5 h-5 text-[#064161] transform transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
          </svg>
        </button>
        <div class="accordion-content hidden px-6 py-4">
          <div class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-[#064161] space-y-4">
            <!-- Subsections -->
            <div class="border-l-4 border-[#FEE96A] pl-4">
              In the US, before the counterculture detonated, people were mainly hearing rock ’n’ roll’s second wave, folk revival (Woody Guthrie → Bob Dylan), gospel, soul, and jazz. The mainstream was still dominated by crooners, Broadway, and polished studio pop.
            </div>
            <div class="border-l-4 border-[#C13870] pl-4">
              In the UK, skiffle (Lonnie Donegan, early Beatles) and dancehall-style pop ruled, with trad jazz and R&B imports from America forming the early underground.
            </div>
            <div class="border-l-4 border-[#FEE96A] pl-4">
              Indigenous traditions also carry influence: blues from the American South, gospel choirs, and Afro-Caribbean immigrant communities in London bringing ska, mento, and calypso into youth soundtracks.
            </div>
            
          
          </div>

          
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- What you can find in this playlist -->
      <div class="accordion-item bg-white border border-[#FEE96A]/30 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
        <button class="accordion-trigger w-full px-6 py-4 text-left bg-[#FEE96A]/10 hover:bg-[#FEE96A]/20 transition-colors flex justify-between items-center">
          <div class="flex items-center space-x-3">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-[#064161]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 10V3L4 14h7v7l9-11h-7z"></path>
            </svg>
            <h4 class="text-xl text-[#064161]">What you can find in this playlist            </h4>
          </div>
          <svg class="accordion-icon w-5 h-5 text-[#064161] transform transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
          </svg>
        </button>
        <div class="accordion-content hidden px-6 py-4">
          <div class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-[#064161] space-y-6">
            This was the decade when everything fractured and music began spilling outside the neat boxes:
            <div class="border-l-4 border-[#FEE96A] pl-4">
              Garage Rock (US) – Teenage bands in basements banging out proto-punk riffs. Nuggets compilations immortalized the raw, lo-fi rebellion.
            </div>
            <div class="border-l-4 border-[#C13870] pl-4">
              Folk Rock – Dylan goes electric (’65 Newport Festival), sending shockwaves through both folk purists and pop radio.
            </div>
            <div class="border-l-4 border-[#FEE96A] pl-4">
              Free Jazz – Ornette Coleman, Cecil Taylor, Sun Ra — tearing jazz away from swing and chord charts into cosmic anarchy.
            </div>
            <div class="border-l-4 border-[#C13870] pl-4">
              Minimalism – La Monte Young, Terry Riley, Steve Reich, Philip Glass: the downtown NYC school shifting music toward drones, repetition, and process.
            </div>
            <div class="border-l-4 border-[#FEE96A] pl-4">
              Psychedelia – West Coast US bands (Jefferson Airplane, Grateful Dead) vs. UK’s London underground (Pink Floyd, Soft Machine) — mind expansion as sound design.
            </div>
            <div class="border-l-4 border-[#C13870] pl-4">
              Avant-Garde Rock – Velvet Underground in NYC and AMM in London, crossing noise, performance art, and rock structures.
            </div>
            <div class="border-l-4 border-[#FEE96A] pl-4">
              Electronic Experiments – Delia Derbyshire and the BBC Radiophonic Workshop in the UK, Morton Subotnick and Pauline Oliveros in the US — pushing tape manipulation and early synths.
            </div>
            <div class="border-l-4 border-[#C13870] pl-4">
              Improvised collectives – The UK’s Spontaneous Music Ensemble, the US’s Association for the Advancement of Creative Musicians (AACM) in Chicago. Improvisation as liberation.
            </div>
          </div>
           

        </div>
      </div>


      <!-- The Tech Factor -->
      <div class="accordion-item bg-white border border-[#FEE96A]/30 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
        <button class="accordion-trigger w-full px-6 py-4 text-left bg-[#FEE96A]/10 hover:bg-[#FEE96A]/20 transition-colors flex justify-between items-center">
          <div class="flex items-center space-x-3">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-[#064161]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9.75 17L9 20l-1 1h8l-1-1-.75-3M3 13h18M5 17h14a2 2 0 002-2V5a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2z"></path>
            </svg>
            <h4 class="text-xl text-[#064161]">Technological changes </h4>
          </div>
          <svg class="accordion-icon w-5 h-5 text-[#064161] transform transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
          </svg>
        </button>
        <div class="accordion-content hidden px-6 py-4">
          <div class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-[#064161] space-y-4">
            The 1960s saw a revolution in how music was made, recorded, and heard:
            <div class="border-l-4 border-[#FEE96A] pl-4">
              Amplification – Marshall stacks, Fender amps, and distortion pedals changed the role of guitars forever.
            </div>
            <div class="border-l-4 border-[#C13870] pl-4">
              Tape Manipulation – Looping, reverse playback, splicing — pioneered at both Cologne and Paris studios, but embraced by psychedelia and avant-garde.
            </div>
            <div class="border-l-4 border-[#FEE96A] pl-4">
              Synths – The Moog synthesizer appeared in the late ’60s (Switched-On Bach by Wendy Carlos). Early modular synths were used by Subotnick (Silver Apples of the Moon).
            </div>
            <div class="border-l-4 border-[#C13870] pl-4">
              Studios as Instruments – The Beatles with George Martin at Abbey Road; Brian Wilson with the Beach Boys on Pet Sounds. Multitrack recording became an experimental tool, not just documentation.
            </div>
            <div class="border-l-4 border-[#FEE96A] pl-4">
              DIY Spaces – From lofts in NYC (Fluxus happenings, Oliveros’s Sonic Meditations) to art schools in the UK (the birthplace of many bands), experimentation needed new spaces outside classical institutions.
            </div>
            </div>


            
          
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Notable Artists -->
      <div class="accordion-item bg-white border border-[#FEE96A]/30 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
        <button class="accordion-trigger w-full px-6 py-4 text-left bg-[#FEE96A]/10 hover:bg-[#FEE96A]/20 transition-colors flex justify-between items-center">
          <div class="flex items-center space-x-3">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-[#064161]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M16 7a4 4 0 11-8 0 4 4 0 018 0zM12 14a7 7 0 00-7 7h14a7 7 0 00-7-7z"></path>
            </svg>
              <h4 class="text-xl text-[#064161]">Notable Artists</h4>
          </div>
          <svg class="accordion-icon w-5 h-5 text-[#064161] transform transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
          </svg>
        </button>
        <div class="accordion-content hidden px-6 py-4">
          <div class="space-y-6">
            {data.notable_artists.map((region, index) => (
              <div>
                <h5 class={`text-lg font-bold text-[#064161] mb-4 border-b-2  pb-2 ${index%2==0? 'border-[#FEE96A]' : 'border-[#C13870]'}`}>{region.title}</h5>
                <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
                  {region.artists.map((artist) => (
                    <div class={`${index%3==0? 'bg-[#FEE96A]/10' : 'bg-[#C13870]/10'} p-4 rounded-lg border border-[#C13870]/30`}>
                     
                      {artist.image && <img src={artist.image} alt={artist.name} class="w-24 h-24 rounded-full object-cover">}
                      <h6 class="font-bold text-[#064161]">{artist.name}</h6>
                      <p class="text-sm text-[#064161]/80">{artist.description}</p>
                    </div>
                  ))}
                </div>
              </div>
            ))}
              </div>
            
          
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>


</div>

<script>
  // Accordion functionality
  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
    const accordionTriggers = document.querySelectorAll('.accordion-trigger');
    
    accordionTriggers.forEach(trigger => {
      trigger.addEventListener('click', () => {
        const accordionItem = trigger.closest('.accordion-item');
        const content = accordionItem?.querySelector('.accordion-content');
        const icon = trigger.querySelector('.accordion-icon');
        
        if (content && icon) {
          const isOpen = !content.classList.contains('hidden');
          

          
          // Toggle current accordion
          if (isOpen) {
            content.classList.add('hidden');
            icon.classList.remove('rotate-180');
          } else {
            content.classList.remove('hidden');
            icon.classList.add('rotate-180');
          }
        }
      });
    });
  });
</script>


